WEBVTT

00:02.176 --> 00:05.875
Banana blueberry
with a hint of cinnamon.

00:07.137 --> 00:08.095
I think
it's my best yet.

00:08.269 --> 00:10.401
Hm.
I like chocolate chip...

00:10.575 --> 00:12.534
Mmm....with syrup.

00:12.708 --> 00:14.579
I like eating pancakes
in bed.

00:14.753 --> 00:16.668
Do you want to
- have sex again?
- Yes.

00:16.842 --> 00:17.887
Do you want to finish
the pancakes first?

00:19.497 --> 00:20.498
- Yes.
- Me too.

00:20.672 --> 00:22.283
[CHUCKLES]

00:22.457 --> 00:24.937
We are very good
at pretending to be married,

00:25.112 --> 00:27.114
but we are very bad
at getting married.

00:27.288 --> 00:29.377
I don't want to
do it anymore.

00:29.551 --> 00:32.075
Not the marriage,
the wedding.

00:32.249 --> 00:34.599
I don't want any more
dress fittings or guest lists.

00:34.773 --> 00:36.384
I just want to be married.

00:39.822 --> 00:41.128
Shaun...[KEYS CLACKING]

00:41.302 --> 00:43.521
...we have 45 more minutes
of our fake honeymoon.

00:43.695 --> 00:45.088
No work.

00:47.569 --> 00:49.962
There is an opening at
the courthouse tomorrow
at 4:30.

00:54.402 --> 00:55.751
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

00:55.925 --> 00:56.839
Cheese, no.
Peppers, yes?

00:57.013 --> 00:58.928
Perfect.

00:59.102 --> 01:01.713
[CELLPHONE VIBRATES]

01:01.887 --> 01:03.498
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

01:03.672 --> 01:06.022
Is that him?

01:06.196 --> 01:07.458
Based on the last
three voicemails,

01:07.632 --> 01:10.287
he's calling about
the restraining order I filed.

01:10.461 --> 01:13.682
- How are you feeling?
- Like my future is a dark,
formless void,

01:13.856 --> 01:15.945
which makes it
full of possibility.

01:16.119 --> 01:17.816
Like a one-bed,
one-bath rental.

01:17.990 --> 01:20.210
You've only been here
a few days.

01:20.384 --> 01:22.517
Which is a few days longer
than anyone should crash

01:22.691 --> 01:23.083
on their boss's couch.

01:25.520 --> 01:26.782
Thank you, Audrey.

01:26.956 --> 01:28.131
Thank you.

01:29.785 --> 01:32.222
Why am I watching you
make a smoothie?

01:32.396 --> 01:34.311
You're watching me dance
while I make a smoothie.

01:34.485 --> 01:35.921
It's not a smoothie
if it has tequila in it.

01:36.096 --> 01:37.923
It's a spinach and flax seed
margarita.

01:38.098 --> 01:39.099
Hey!
And it makes you dance.

01:39.273 --> 01:40.622
Mm.

01:40.796 --> 01:42.189
Okay, listen...
No.

01:42.363 --> 01:43.320
[GRUNTING]
Too much butt, though.

01:43.494 --> 01:44.147
Think about the butt.[LAUGHING]

01:44.321 --> 01:45.670
Asher?

01:52.503 --> 01:54.201
What are you doing here?

01:54.375 --> 01:56.159
[SPEAKING HEBREW]

02:00.729 --> 02:01.904
Meet my parents.

02:06.735 --> 02:09.258
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

02:16.614 --> 02:18.007
Steph Lewis, 35.

02:18.181 --> 02:20.183
She had a brainstem stroke
nine years ago

02:20.357 --> 02:23.099
that left her paralyzed
from her face down.

02:23.273 --> 02:24.622
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
<i>I still have</i>
<i>10% movement in three fingers</i>

02:24.796 --> 02:27.190
<i>so don't sell me short.</i>

02:27.364 --> 02:30.802
W... How'd you type that
so quickly?

02:30.976 --> 02:32.456
<i>I have eight different</i>
<i>pre-programmed phrases</i>

02:32.630 --> 02:33.327
<i>to put people at ease.</i>

02:35.851 --> 02:38.419
She's had four serious bouts
of pneumonia

02:38.593 --> 02:40.160
in the last few months.

02:40.334 --> 02:42.814
Um, she's taken levofloxacin
for the infection

02:42.988 --> 02:45.643
and glycopyrrolate
for the trach secretions,

02:45.817 --> 02:47.950
but she still has high fever,
decreased energy,
night sweats.

02:48.124 --> 02:50.822
<i>He's so sexy</i>
<i>when he talks medical.</i>

02:50.996 --> 02:52.172
DR. RESNICK: The pneumonia
caused scar tissue,

02:52.346 --> 02:53.303
which is compressing
her lung.

02:53.477 --> 02:55.218
She needs surgical
decortication.

02:55.392 --> 02:57.089
That's a pretty aggressive
approach.

02:57.264 --> 02:59.004
Surgery comes
with serious risk,

02:59.179 --> 03:01.485
recurrent air leaks,
respiratory failure, sepsis.

03:01.659 --> 03:03.574
And giving round after round
of antibiotics

03:03.748 --> 03:05.272
is only going to make
the infections harder to...

03:05.446 --> 03:07.448
<i>Hello.</i>

03:07.622 --> 03:09.450
[CONTROLLER CLACKING]

03:12.670 --> 03:15.673
<i>I want the surgery.</i>

03:15.847 --> 03:18.459
[CONTROLLER CLACKING]

03:18.633 --> 03:20.809
<i>I know the risks.</i>
<i>I'm sick of feeling crappy.</i>

03:31.254 --> 03:33.213
YOSEL: I have terminal
lung cancer.

03:33.387 --> 03:35.215
Doctors say I have
less than a year

03:35.389 --> 03:37.217
and no good surgical options.

03:39.654 --> 03:43.310
I'm... So sorry.

03:43.484 --> 03:45.442
We're not here
for sympathy.

03:45.616 --> 03:48.663
God, in his wisdom,
gave us a son

03:48.837 --> 03:51.535
who would grow up to be
a doctor for times like this.

03:51.709 --> 03:54.408
He will work a miracle
through you.

04:09.031 --> 04:09.988
I can't do lunch today.
I have a job interview

04:10.162 --> 04:11.599
with New York Medical Center.

04:11.773 --> 04:12.991
I didn't know you were
considering positions

04:13.165 --> 04:14.515
on the other side
of the country.

04:14.689 --> 04:16.560
I'm not. I just want to
get multiple offers

04:16.733 --> 04:18.127
so I can leverage a better one
from St. Bon's.

04:18.301 --> 04:20.434
Makes you look in demand.

04:20.608 --> 04:22.262
Uh, I'd rather look like
I want the job I have now.

04:22.436 --> 04:24.481
SHAUN: Oh, hello.

04:24.655 --> 04:26.570
- Hi.
- Yes.

04:26.744 --> 04:30.052
Um, thank you so much
for your gift, whatever it is.

04:30.226 --> 04:32.010
We are returning it.

04:32.184 --> 04:33.664
We're getting married
at the courthouse tomorrow.

04:33.838 --> 04:35.449
And since neither of you
are invited,

04:35.623 --> 04:38.234
Weddiquette.org said we're
supposed to return the gift.

04:38.408 --> 04:40.105
Excellent. I can exchange it
for store credit.

04:40.280 --> 04:42.151
That's exciting.

04:42.325 --> 04:44.153
They're getting married where
people pay parking tickets.

04:44.327 --> 04:45.589
[CELLPHONE VIBRATES]
What about
a destination wedding?

04:45.763 --> 04:47.765
Hmm. We're good.

04:47.939 --> 04:49.680
I have to go.
We are going to be

04:49.854 --> 04:51.856
husband and wife
- in 30 hours and 27 minutes.
- Mm. Mm.

04:54.772 --> 04:56.513
Stage four lung cancer

04:56.687 --> 04:57.906
which has invaded
the chest wall.

04:58.080 --> 04:59.908
Six rounds of chemo.
The treatment has caused

05:00.082 --> 05:01.692
severe anemia and colitis.

05:01.866 --> 05:03.912
Your hair is flatter.

05:04.086 --> 05:05.870
We need a CT of the chest,
abdomen, and pelvis,

05:06.044 --> 05:08.395
CBC, blood cultures,
and an EKG.

05:08.569 --> 05:10.875
I will review your results
with Dr. Andrews,

05:11.049 --> 05:13.356
and we will try to find
a treatment to help you.

05:13.530 --> 05:14.966
God bless you,
Dr. Murphy.

05:15.140 --> 05:16.968
Okay, thank you.

05:23.279 --> 05:24.715
Can you guys cool it

05:24.889 --> 05:25.890
with the blessing people
in the name of God?

05:26.064 --> 05:27.631
This is
a secular hospital.

05:27.805 --> 05:29.372
It's called
Saint Bonaventure.

05:31.809 --> 05:33.637
Mr. and Mrs. Wolke,
I'm Jerome.

05:33.811 --> 05:35.552
We met briefly
this morning.

05:35.726 --> 05:36.466
I'm gonna draw some blood.

05:37.946 --> 05:38.903
Jerome is...

05:40.383 --> 05:41.384
A nurse.

05:43.255 --> 05:44.518
Jerome is your nurse.

05:48.826 --> 05:50.350
The surgery went well.

05:50.524 --> 05:51.612
We removed
all of the scar tissue,

05:51.786 --> 05:53.701
and the lung expanded
completely.

05:53.875 --> 05:55.964
- Thank you.
- Mm.

05:56.138 --> 05:57.008
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

05:57.182 --> 05:58.227
[MONITOR BEEPING]

06:02.013 --> 06:03.014
Why can't she
move her hand?

06:09.760 --> 06:12.284
Steph, can you blink
when you feel something?

06:17.812 --> 06:19.030
What's going on?

06:24.645 --> 06:25.950
Will it come back?

06:27.691 --> 06:29.258
I don't know.

06:44.578 --> 06:46.144
I read your letter

06:46.318 --> 06:48.625
a few months ago.

06:48.799 --> 06:50.540
I sent it six years ago.

06:53.891 --> 06:55.980
I wasn't sure I wanted to hear
what you had to say.

06:58.200 --> 06:59.810
But it was nice.

07:04.162 --> 07:05.860
I just wanted to tell you
about the family.

07:09.341 --> 07:12.214
I'm not a part
of the family anymore.

07:12.388 --> 07:15.217
You made that very clear
when I left.

07:15.391 --> 07:16.610
You chose to leave.

07:19.613 --> 07:23.921
We wanted you to stay,
wanted to help you.

07:24.095 --> 07:25.575
You're not the only one
who struggles

07:25.749 --> 07:29.057
with finding
the right path.

07:29.231 --> 07:31.581
We all must sometimes choose
to deny our flesh.

07:36.717 --> 07:37.500
You're right.

07:39.546 --> 07:41.722
I did make a choice.

07:41.896 --> 07:43.854
I could follow your rules,

07:44.028 --> 07:47.031
or I could love and accept
who I am.

07:49.556 --> 07:52.950
I chose which one
mattered more...

07:53.124 --> 07:54.691
And so did you.

07:56.867 --> 08:00.001
[STRAINED BREATHING]

08:00.175 --> 08:02.307
Are you okay?

08:02.482 --> 08:03.570
Take a deep breath.

08:03.744 --> 08:05.746
[SHALLOW WHEEZING]

08:09.924 --> 08:11.055
I need some help!

08:18.410 --> 08:21.239
CT shows the chest wall tumor
has grown.

08:21.413 --> 08:23.024
He's bleeding into
the thoracic cavity,
and it is collapsing his lung.

08:23.198 --> 08:24.895
He needs surgery
to stop the bleed now.

08:25.069 --> 08:26.157
His blood cell counts
are too low.

08:26.331 --> 08:27.855
Maybe we should do an echo
to see if his heart

08:28.029 --> 08:29.247
is stable enough for--No. There isn't time.

08:29.421 --> 08:30.771
Get consent from your mother,
and I will start

08:30.945 --> 08:32.860
prepping your father
for the embolization.

08:33.034 --> 08:33.904
The anesthesia
must have caused

08:34.078 --> 08:35.210
a drop in
Steph's blood pressure

08:35.384 --> 08:36.864
and completed
her previous injury.

08:37.038 --> 08:38.169
Then her best bet's
eye-tracking technology.

08:38.342 --> 08:40.389
That'll be great,

08:40.563 --> 08:41.738
as long as she only wants
to speak one word a minute.

08:41.912 --> 08:43.174
Well, she'll get
the hang of it.

08:43.347 --> 08:44.785
After months of training.

08:44.959 --> 08:47.048
Well, it's better than
what she has now.

08:47.222 --> 08:48.528
How'd the interview go?

08:48.702 --> 08:50.573
Mm. Great.

08:50.747 --> 08:52.096
The head
of internal medicine

08:52.270 --> 08:53.620
is basically me
10 years from now.

08:53.794 --> 08:55.622
We loved each other.

08:55.796 --> 08:57.885
And her department just got
a SPORE grant.

08:58.059 --> 08:59.277
Sounds like
you're interested.

08:59.451 --> 09:00.452
It sounds like I'm answering
your question.

09:00.627 --> 09:02.193
Oh, with enthusiasm.

09:02.367 --> 09:04.413
Wha... What am I gonna do
with a second blender?

09:06.197 --> 09:07.764
Yeah, I got you a blender.

09:09.984 --> 09:11.072
JORDAN: <i>Open it.</i>

09:11.246 --> 09:13.378
Weddiquette says I can't.

09:13.553 --> 09:15.729
That's dumb.
Just open it.

09:18.775 --> 09:20.255
Oh, I can't.

09:20.429 --> 09:21.082
[WHISPERING]
Just open it.

09:21.256 --> 09:22.431
[SIGHS]

09:25.521 --> 09:26.696
Mm.

09:29.786 --> 09:31.135
[PAPER RUSTLES]

09:35.923 --> 09:37.794
[GASPS]

09:38.969 --> 09:41.232
I really love it.

09:41.406 --> 09:43.539
Mm-hmm. The photo's
just a placeholder

09:43.713 --> 09:46.107
until you get the real
- wedding pics.
- Mm.

09:46.281 --> 09:48.109
But that dress
looked amazing on you.

09:48.283 --> 09:50.154
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

09:52.853 --> 09:54.158
- This was fun.
- Mm-hmm.

10:14.178 --> 10:15.353
Your blood pressure
looks good.

10:15.527 --> 10:17.921
No fever
or sign of infection.

10:18.095 --> 10:19.183
We should be able to start you
on eye-tracking tomorrow.

10:21.055 --> 10:23.274
W... We tried that before.

10:23.448 --> 10:25.320
It can take a while
to get used to.

10:25.494 --> 10:26.843
[MONITOR BEEPING]

10:30.630 --> 10:32.849
[STEPH LAUGHS]

10:33.023 --> 10:33.894
JULIAN: <i>No, no, the camera's</i>
<i>facing the right way</i>
<i>this time.</i>

10:34.068 --> 10:36.897
<i>I promise.</i> [STEPH LAUGHS]

10:37.071 --> 10:38.986
STEPH:
<i>This is the living room.</i>

10:39.160 --> 10:43.077
<i>Also the dining room, kitchen,</i>
<i>guest room, and office.</i>

10:43.251 --> 10:45.383
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

10:45.557 --> 10:48.169
<i>All conveniently located</i>
<i>in these 400 square feet.</i>

10:48.343 --> 10:49.649
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

10:49.823 --> 10:51.520
<i>And it's all ours!</i>

10:53.478 --> 10:55.219
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

10:57.744 --> 10:59.571
[LAUGHS]

11:01.225 --> 11:03.358
[CELLPHONE RINGING]
Someone's phone's ringing.

11:03.532 --> 11:05.969
I know.[RINGING CONTINUES]

11:06.143 --> 11:07.884
DR. RESNICK: Park.

11:08.058 --> 11:09.059
We can give Steph
her voice back.

11:12.933 --> 11:15.457
Advance the catheter to
the right fourth
intercostal artery.

11:15.631 --> 11:16.850
[MONITOR BEEPING,
RESPIRATOR HISSING]

11:20.810 --> 11:24.379
He got this scar teaching me
how to ride a bike.

11:24.553 --> 11:26.860
I was going too fast.
I didn't know how to
brake yet.

11:27.034 --> 11:29.689
He caught me.

11:29.863 --> 11:31.255
We both ended up
with stitches.

11:34.389 --> 11:37.261
Delivering
the embolic agent.

11:37.435 --> 11:40.525
My dad taught me
how to tie a tie.

11:40.700 --> 11:43.572
He was a minister who wore
his Sunday best

11:43.746 --> 11:45.356
every day of the week.

11:45.530 --> 11:48.359
When he died,

11:48.533 --> 11:51.275
I wore his suit jackets
every day for a year.

11:53.625 --> 11:56.324
My dad was my first
chemistry teacher.

11:56.498 --> 11:59.936
We baked together every
weekend on a quest to find

12:00.110 --> 12:02.765
the perfect oatmeal
chocolate chip cookie recipe.

12:02.939 --> 12:04.071
[CHUCKLES]

12:12.122 --> 12:14.211
I'm cold.

12:14.385 --> 12:15.778
ANDREW:
Fluid is cloudy.

12:17.780 --> 12:19.303
He has a malignant
pleural effusion.

12:20.565 --> 12:22.176
Can we drain it?

12:22.350 --> 12:24.613
It will keep coming back

12:24.787 --> 12:27.181
and spread the cancer
everywhere in
his chest cavity.

12:30.662 --> 12:33.100
Your father's prognosis
was wrong.

12:33.274 --> 12:34.841
He only has
a few weeks to live.

12:47.157 --> 12:49.333
You have weeks.
Maybe days.

12:50.465 --> 12:52.293
But likely weeks.

12:52.467 --> 12:54.599
DR. ANDREWS: We'll continue
to drain the fluid

12:54.774 --> 12:55.862
and try to find a surgery
that will give you more time.

13:00.823 --> 13:03.695
God has privileged us
with great miracles.

13:05.915 --> 13:07.351
And He will again.

13:12.052 --> 13:13.357
<i>Shabbos.</i>

13:17.579 --> 13:20.669
The Jewish holy day of rest
begins tonight.

13:20.843 --> 13:25.369
God and I plan to do
just that...

13:25.543 --> 13:26.370
Rest.

13:28.024 --> 13:28.982
Okay, let's...

13:32.550 --> 13:34.901
We'll implant electrodes
on her sensorimotor cortex,

13:35.075 --> 13:36.859
which will decode
her brainwaves.

13:37.033 --> 13:38.948
All Steph has to do
is try to speak,

13:39.122 --> 13:40.384
and the receiver relays
the signals,

13:40.558 --> 13:42.256
which are translated
into speech.

13:42.430 --> 13:44.084
It's brand-new technology

13:44.258 --> 13:46.216
that's only been done
successfully a couple times.

13:46.390 --> 13:47.827
It's new technology that would
give Steph not just a voice,

13:48.001 --> 13:50.220
but her voice back.

13:50.394 --> 13:52.483
By uploading audio files taken
before the stroke, we can...

13:52.657 --> 13:55.312
But Steph can't handle another
life-threatening surgery.

13:55.486 --> 13:56.836
The eye-tracking device will
allow her to communicate...

13:57.010 --> 14:00.317
Right now,
they've got nothing.

14:00.491 --> 14:02.232
They love each other.

14:02.406 --> 14:04.147
You're pushing false hope
because you see Steph

14:04.321 --> 14:05.845
as nothing but a burden.

14:06.019 --> 14:09.457
I'm trying to give them
some quality of life.

14:09.631 --> 14:11.372
You're risking her life
because you can't imagine

14:11.546 --> 14:13.417
making that kind of sacrifice
for another person.

14:13.591 --> 14:14.418
LIM: Park's right.

14:16.943 --> 14:18.727
It's risky.
But it's not false hope.

14:18.901 --> 14:20.381
Let's take it to them,

14:20.555 --> 14:22.774
without any hint of whatever's
going on between you.

14:34.699 --> 14:37.180
[SIGHS]
No one is coming into

14:37.354 --> 14:38.616
a patient's room
to turn on the TV.

14:38.790 --> 14:40.357
[GRUNTS]

14:40.531 --> 14:43.099
And this way,
I can ensure it.

14:43.273 --> 14:44.448
[MONITOR BEEPING]

14:49.410 --> 14:50.890
Okay,
if you want him to breathe
through <i>Shabbos,</i>

14:51.064 --> 14:52.326
I suggest you leave those
plugged in.

14:52.500 --> 14:53.980
[CHUCKLES]

14:55.155 --> 14:56.721
Hi, family.

14:56.896 --> 14:59.681
- Hello.
- How's your pain?

14:59.855 --> 15:00.943
It's nothing
I can't handle.

15:05.339 --> 15:07.297
[GRUNTS]

15:07.471 --> 15:08.733
Will you join us for <i>Shabbos,</i>
Dr. Allen?

15:10.605 --> 15:13.913
Uh, I'd love to,

15:14.087 --> 15:16.611
but I should be researching
how to save your life.

15:16.785 --> 15:18.482
Am I dying tomorrow?

15:20.963 --> 15:22.660
Then <i>Shabbos</i>
is more important.

15:22.834 --> 15:24.793
From sundown to sundown,

15:24.967 --> 15:29.232
we devote a day to joy
and God.

15:29.406 --> 15:31.495
How can I say no to God?

15:39.547 --> 15:43.290
[CHANTING IN HEBREW]

15:45.596 --> 15:46.771
[HUMMING]

16:16.584 --> 16:18.890
[CHANTING IN HEBREW]

16:26.376 --> 16:28.378
<i>♪♪ Blue</i>

16:32.382 --> 16:35.559
<i>♪♪ To green</i>

16:39.520 --> 16:46.092
<i>♪♪ So quickly</i>

16:54.187 --> 17:00.802
<i>♪♪ Whispered words</i>

17:06.415 --> 17:12.117
<i>♪♪ So sweetly</i>

17:12.291 --> 17:14.816
I'm sorry.

17:14.990 --> 17:18.950
I was projecting
and overreacted.

17:19.125 --> 17:20.300
An interview is
just an interview.

17:20.473 --> 17:21.910
They offered me the job.

17:23.651 --> 17:28.308
<i>♪♪ Whispered words ♪♪</i>

17:31.311 --> 17:35.271
Asher, will you say
the <i>mischa beruch</i> for <i>Abba?</i>

17:35.445 --> 17:38.013
Prayer for the sick,
for his father.

17:41.625 --> 17:42.974
You want me to pray to a God
I don't believe in?

17:47.631 --> 17:51.331
Why can't you honor me
in my last days on Earth?

17:51.505 --> 17:52.375
These aren't
your last days.

17:52.549 --> 17:53.898
You told me...

17:54.073 --> 17:55.117
We're finding
a surgical solution.

17:58.338 --> 17:59.861
[INHALES SHARPLY]

18:02.951 --> 18:05.388
I am dying.

18:05.562 --> 18:06.302
I have accepted that.

18:06.476 --> 18:07.651
Yosel.

18:10.263 --> 18:12.047
I'm sorry, Miriam.

18:16.573 --> 18:21.665
What I want is
to go to God at peace.

18:24.538 --> 18:27.410
I want you to come home.

18:27.584 --> 18:30.979
Be with me and your mother

18:31.153 --> 18:33.242
and your brothers
and sisters.

18:42.251 --> 18:44.688
[CHUCKLES]

18:46.081 --> 18:48.257
It's sad.

18:53.175 --> 18:55.960
I want to be your son...

18:56.135 --> 18:57.701
Almost more than
I want to be myself.

19:00.530 --> 19:02.010
But I can't.

19:15.589 --> 19:17.156
This is who I am.

19:18.896 --> 19:20.724
And this is my boyfriend.

19:42.877 --> 19:45.488
You have been acting
differently.

19:45.662 --> 19:47.316
Is it because you think

19:47.490 --> 19:48.448
it will make your parents
like you more

19:48.622 --> 19:52.408
if you act more...
More...

19:52.582 --> 19:54.584
- Straight?
- Mm.

19:54.758 --> 19:59.023
I think they'd like me more
if I actually was straight.

19:59.198 --> 20:00.938
My parents would have
liked me better

20:01.112 --> 20:02.984
if I didn't have autism.

20:03.158 --> 20:04.899
But your dad
is not like my dad.

20:05.073 --> 20:07.118
Your dad came to see you.

20:07.293 --> 20:08.685
Mm.

20:08.859 --> 20:11.297
The effusion fluid is
reaccumulating

20:11.471 --> 20:14.169
faster than
we can drain it.

20:14.343 --> 20:15.518
[SIGHS]

20:15.692 --> 20:18.173
The tumor's like a faucet
we can't turn off.

20:18.347 --> 20:21.785
It's spraying cancer-water
everywhere.

20:21.959 --> 20:25.006
That is
an interesting simile.

20:39.499 --> 20:40.848
We can't turn it off,

20:41.022 --> 20:42.066
but we can give it
nowhere to go.

20:42.850 --> 20:44.765
Hm.

20:44.939 --> 20:47.507
SHAUN:
By injecting the pleural
cavity with a slurry of talc,

20:47.681 --> 20:49.857
inflammation and scarring
will fill up the space,

20:50.031 --> 20:52.468
clogging up
the tumor and giving
it nowhere to leak fluid into.

20:52.642 --> 20:54.340
ASHER: And after you heal
from the surgery,

20:54.514 --> 20:56.559
we'll try an experimental
targeted immunotherapy.

20:56.733 --> 20:58.387
It should give you a year,
maybe more.

20:58.561 --> 21:00.694
<i>Ko vay hashem</i>
<i>Yah-chalifu Koach.</i>

21:00.868 --> 21:03.349
How long is the recovery?

21:06.177 --> 21:08.615
You will have to
stay in the hospital

21:08.789 --> 21:11.618
for at least one week.

21:11.792 --> 21:14.577
What are the chances
I'll survive it,

21:14.751 --> 21:16.797
the surgery, the treatment?

21:16.971 --> 21:20.366
There are risks of both,
but we're confident...

21:20.540 --> 21:24.065
I don't want to die away
from home and my family.

21:31.681 --> 21:33.509
We're giving you
more time.

21:33.683 --> 21:34.293
Please take it.

21:43.345 --> 21:45.129
Okay.

21:46.261 --> 21:46.914
Okay.

21:48.742 --> 21:49.873
<i>Baruch hashem.</i>

22:04.627 --> 22:05.846
Excuse me.
I have flowers for...

22:06.020 --> 22:07.500
Someone else
can take them.

22:11.286 --> 22:15.377
LIM: Exposing the sensorimotor
cortex of the left hemisphere.

22:15.551 --> 22:19.381
Electrode array is prepped
for implantation.

22:19.555 --> 22:22.079
I heard Morgan got a job offer
in New York.

22:22.253 --> 22:25.648
- Yeah.
- Tough call for her.

22:25.822 --> 22:28.869
As long as she's at St. Bon's,
she'll be seen as

22:29.043 --> 22:31.350
the doctor who used to be
a surgeon but
can't be anymore.

22:34.048 --> 22:35.919
5-0 prolene on a castro
to suture the dura.

22:39.923 --> 22:42.361
The AI will take samples from
a variety of cortical regions

22:42.535 --> 22:43.927
that are used
in speech processing,

22:44.101 --> 22:45.625
and the predictive analytics
should...

22:45.799 --> 22:47.844
Would you work faster if you
didn't explain every step?

22:48.018 --> 22:49.455
Mm.

22:49.629 --> 22:51.457
STEPH:
<i>To have and to hold,</i>

22:51.631 --> 22:54.460
<i>to honor, to treasure,</i>

22:54.634 --> 22:58.464
<i>to be at his side</i>
<i>in sorrow and in joy,</i>

22:58.638 --> 22:59.290
<i>in the good times</i>
<i>and in the bad...</i>

22:59.465 --> 23:01.423
[CHUCKLES]

23:01.597 --> 23:04.383
<i>...and to love</i>
<i>and cherish always.</i>

23:04.557 --> 23:06.602
<i>I love you.</i>

23:06.776 --> 23:07.734
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

23:14.784 --> 23:16.699
You're being a jerk.

23:16.873 --> 23:18.484
You think I'm being a jerk
to the people
that want me to be

23:18.658 --> 23:20.964
the godly, straight person
I never was?

23:26.361 --> 23:27.928
For the two years
I've known you,

23:28.102 --> 23:32.411
you have been cute and funny
and clever

23:32.585 --> 23:36.023
and caring and sensitive.

23:37.938 --> 23:41.942
Suddenly, your parents show up
and you're just angry.

23:42.116 --> 23:42.986
I think I have
every right to be.

23:46.903 --> 23:47.817
Why do you think
he came here?

23:47.991 --> 23:49.297
So I could save his life

23:49.471 --> 23:51.255
and send him back
to his real family.

23:51.430 --> 23:54.998
Asher, he would have
found a reason

23:55.172 --> 23:58.349
to get on that plane
if you were a car mechanic.

23:58.524 --> 24:01.135
He came here for peace.

24:01.309 --> 24:03.006
Not a miracle cure.

24:06.227 --> 24:08.403
[SIGHS] We have
two minutes in total

24:08.577 --> 24:10.492
at the courthouse
to say our vows.

24:10.666 --> 24:12.842
My vows are 26 seconds
if I'm talking slowly,

24:13.016 --> 24:15.584
which I might because
it is an important moment.

24:15.758 --> 24:17.630
Is one minute and 34 seconds
enough time for you?

24:20.850 --> 24:22.896
- Lea?
- Sorry.

24:23.070 --> 24:25.551
Yeah, it is.

24:25.725 --> 24:26.856
You don't sound happy.

24:29.293 --> 24:30.730
Do you not like
Jordan's wedding gift?

24:30.904 --> 24:32.471
No, it's beautiful.

24:32.645 --> 24:34.560
It's just a reminder
that I'll never

24:34.734 --> 24:37.171
wear a real wedding gown
at my dream wedding.

24:37.345 --> 24:40.130
That's kind of a bummer.

24:40.304 --> 24:43.569
Have you changed your mind
about the courthouse?

24:43.743 --> 24:46.441
No. In those dreams,

24:46.615 --> 24:49.400
you are the only constant,
Shaun.

24:49.575 --> 24:52.491
Just the two of us,
that's enough for me.

24:52.665 --> 24:54.057
[SIGHS]

25:02.675 --> 25:04.546
- Shaun?
- I'm confused.

25:04.720 --> 25:06.417
Okay.

25:06.592 --> 25:08.768
I think I'm getting
mixed signals.

25:08.942 --> 25:10.465
Well, that's a good thing,
isn't it?

25:10.639 --> 25:13.642
Is it?
It doesn't feel like it is.

25:13.816 --> 25:16.297
Well,
you don't normally pick up
on non-verbal cues, right?

25:16.471 --> 25:18.647
That's quite a leap.

25:18.821 --> 25:20.170
Lea says she's disappointed

25:20.344 --> 25:22.172
that we are having our wedding
at the courthouse,

25:22.346 --> 25:23.565
but she also says
she wants to

25:23.739 --> 25:25.785
have our wedding
at the courthouse.

25:25.959 --> 25:28.178
Not quite as big a leap
as I thought, but...

25:28.352 --> 25:29.571
I want to respect
what she wants,

25:29.745 --> 25:32.618
but I also want to respect
her disappointment.

25:32.792 --> 25:35.098
How, How,
How do I do both?

25:35.272 --> 25:36.796
Oh, boy.
[CHUCKLES]

25:36.970 --> 25:38.362
People don't always
know what they want.

25:38.537 --> 25:39.799
But they should.

25:39.973 --> 25:41.844
Especially
if it's a wedding.

25:42.018 --> 25:43.498
Yeah, they should.

25:46.501 --> 25:48.111
Let me think about it.

25:48.285 --> 25:49.112
Excellent.

25:59.383 --> 26:01.255
He wants to die.

26:01.429 --> 26:04.127
He's scared.

26:04.301 --> 26:06.347
I think he's at peace.

26:06.521 --> 26:08.392
He wants to go home,
be with God.

26:10.960 --> 26:12.135
You should let him.

26:14.660 --> 26:16.139
You want me to take
moral advice from you?

26:18.446 --> 26:20.448
You gave that up when...

26:20.622 --> 26:23.059
I lost my morality
when I lost my religion?

26:23.233 --> 26:25.279
Without God, there can be
no objective...

26:25.453 --> 26:27.194
My compassion?
My decency?

26:27.368 --> 26:28.804
You don't really
believe that.

26:31.502 --> 26:34.593
Samuel 1 31:4.

26:34.767 --> 26:37.465
"When Saul saw himself losing
to the Philistines,

26:37.639 --> 26:39.510
"he threw himself on his own
sword to avoid
being captured."

26:39.685 --> 26:40.903
Your father's
not facing torture.

26:41.077 --> 26:43.123
He's with his family.
He's...

26:43.297 --> 26:44.994
He is the one suffering.

26:45.168 --> 26:45.908
He gets to decide.

26:46.082 --> 26:48.868
It's <i>pikuach nefesh!</i>

26:49.042 --> 26:52.393
You do not stand by
while your friend bleeds.

26:52.567 --> 26:54.613
[VOICE BREAKING]
This is not your friend.

26:54.787 --> 26:56.179
This is your father.

26:58.051 --> 27:00.183
This is suicide.

27:00.357 --> 27:01.881
You know there's a difference
between actively taking a life

27:02.055 --> 27:03.796
and passively
letting it go!

27:03.970 --> 27:05.885
And you know that doesn't
let us simply give up.

27:06.059 --> 27:07.364
The principle...[SCOFFS]

27:07.538 --> 27:09.018
If you cared about
principle,

27:09.192 --> 27:11.194
you wouldn't put a timer
on the lights for <i>Shabbos.</i>

27:11.368 --> 27:13.675
If you can find
a way to justify this,
you can justify this!

27:15.111 --> 27:16.939
But you don't want to.

27:18.767 --> 27:20.334
You don't care about
what the Torah says.

27:20.508 --> 27:21.509
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

27:23.816 --> 27:27.558
<i>♪♪ This is what you wanted</i>

27:27.733 --> 27:30.474
People are curious
about my life, my old life.

27:30.649 --> 27:34.174
<i>♪♪ At least that's</i>
<i>what I thought</i>

27:34.348 --> 27:37.873
They ask if I learned
Western history in school,

27:38.047 --> 27:42.530
if I ever saw a TV,
talked to girls,

27:42.704 --> 27:44.401
if my parents had
an arranged marriage.

27:44.575 --> 27:45.968
<i>♪♪ Nothing's ever enough</i>

27:48.318 --> 27:50.016
They're curious
and kind of...

27:50.190 --> 27:52.888
<i>♪♪ Everything is happening now</i>

27:53.062 --> 27:54.020
...appalled by it all.

27:57.893 --> 27:58.677
<i>♪♪ But I'm still having</i>
<i>the hardest time</i>

27:58.851 --> 28:01.418
And the truth is...

28:01.592 --> 28:02.768
<i>♪♪ Hardest time</i>
<i>when all you see</i>

28:02.942 --> 28:05.074
...a lot of it
appalls me.

28:05.248 --> 28:07.424
[VOICE BREAKING] A lot of it
is embarrassing for me.

28:07.598 --> 28:11.167
<i>♪♪ The tide going in and out,</i>
<i>the in-between</i>

28:11.341 --> 28:15.215
But... The one thing
I push back against,

28:15.389 --> 28:18.305
the one thing
I will always defend...

28:18.479 --> 28:19.523
<i>♪♪ You're feeling tired</i>

28:19.698 --> 28:21.525
<i>♪♪ Oh</i>

28:21.700 --> 28:23.484
...is your marriage.

28:23.658 --> 28:24.703
<i>♪♪ It's getting harder</i>
<i>and harder</i>

28:26.574 --> 28:28.663
<i>♪♪ Oh</i> Your love.

28:28.837 --> 28:31.535
<i>♪♪ Keeping my head</i>
<i>above water</i>

28:31.710 --> 28:33.450
[CRYING] I dream of finding
someone to love me

28:33.624 --> 28:34.669
the way you two
love each other.

28:38.194 --> 28:40.631
Mom, you don't want him to die
because you love him.

28:40.806 --> 28:42.285
<i>♪♪ I'm strong enough</i>
<i>to hold my own</i>

28:42.459 --> 28:44.679
<i>♪♪ Hold my own, yeah</i>

28:44.853 --> 28:46.463
That's the only reason.

28:46.637 --> 28:47.769
[SIGHS, SNIFFLES]

28:47.943 --> 28:49.510
It's a very good reason.

28:53.775 --> 28:56.865
<i>♪♪ When all you see</i>

28:57.039 --> 28:57.997
<i>♪♪ The tide going in and out</i>

28:58.171 --> 29:01.870
You don't want the pain
of losing him,

29:02.044 --> 29:04.394
but do you love him enough
to take away his pain?

29:04.568 --> 29:06.570
<i>♪♪ The push and pull</i>
<i>holding you down</i>

29:06.745 --> 29:08.747
To make that pain yours?

29:08.921 --> 29:10.966
<i>♪♪ You're feeling tired</i>

29:11.140 --> 29:12.620
<i>♪♪ Oh</i>

29:12.794 --> 29:15.144
<i>♪♪ It's getting harder</i>
<i>and harder</i>

29:17.756 --> 29:20.367
<i>♪♪ Oh</i>

29:20.541 --> 29:22.978
<i>♪♪ Keeping my head</i>
<i>above water</i>

29:25.067 --> 29:27.374
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

29:27.548 --> 29:29.332
<i>♪♪ Keeping my head</i>
<i>above water</i>

29:34.207 --> 29:36.513
<i>♪♪ Keeping my head</i>
<i>above water ♪♪</i>

29:36.687 --> 29:38.646
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

29:40.169 --> 29:42.432
I'd like to ask you
a favor.

29:42.606 --> 29:44.826
It's gonna cost you.

29:45.000 --> 29:46.610
I don't think it will.

29:50.179 --> 29:51.920
It'll take some time
for the AI

29:52.094 --> 29:53.313
to completely learn
your brain waves,

29:53.487 --> 29:56.359
but you can
give it a try...

29:56.533 --> 29:57.708
When you're ready.

29:57.883 --> 29:59.362
[MONITOR BEEPING]

30:07.588 --> 30:08.371
<i>I love you.</i>

30:17.250 --> 30:18.381
[BREATHES SHARPLY]
I love you, too.

30:22.995 --> 30:24.779
[SNIFFLES]

30:26.085 --> 30:27.390
[SIGHS]

30:33.309 --> 30:34.441
Those from him?

30:34.615 --> 30:36.269
I'm finding them
a good home.

30:38.532 --> 30:40.316
And I found an apartment.

30:40.490 --> 30:42.971
Wow. You only just started
calling me Audrey.

30:43.145 --> 30:44.625
Yes, Dr. Lim, you will have
your place to yourself

30:44.799 --> 30:46.366
within a week.

30:46.540 --> 30:47.715
That's great.

30:51.850 --> 30:54.591
I remember,
my sophomore year of college,

30:54.765 --> 30:56.376
my boyfriend dumped me,

30:56.550 --> 30:57.725
said it was
the honorable thing to do

30:57.899 --> 30:59.335
because he was sleeping
with my roommate.

30:59.509 --> 31:00.423
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

31:00.597 --> 31:03.165
Wrecked me.

31:03.339 --> 31:05.385
Three weeks later, I thought,
"Wow, I am so over that jerk."

31:05.559 --> 31:06.560
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

31:06.734 --> 31:09.084
Three months after that,
I thought,

31:09.258 --> 31:11.695
"Wow,
I can't believe I thought
I was okay after three weeks.

31:11.870 --> 31:13.784
"But now I'm doing okay.

31:13.959 --> 31:16.396
"I'm gonna be fine,
back up on my feet."

31:16.570 --> 31:18.877
Took a year.

31:19.051 --> 31:21.183
Your situation is
obviously different.

31:21.357 --> 31:24.360
And you're more mature,
wiser.

31:24.534 --> 31:26.623
So maybe you are ready.

31:26.797 --> 31:28.451
But on the other hand...

31:31.367 --> 31:33.804
I get used to things,
and right now,

31:33.979 --> 31:35.284
I've gotten used to
your world-class breakfasts.

31:35.458 --> 31:38.722
[CHUCKLES]

31:38.897 --> 31:40.724
Maybe you could give me
a few more weeks?

31:45.773 --> 31:48.210
I'd be honored
to do you that favor.

31:48.384 --> 31:49.646
[CHUCKLES]

31:49.820 --> 31:50.821
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

31:52.258 --> 31:53.476
I need those.

32:00.614 --> 32:03.443
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS,
DOORS OPEN]

32:03.617 --> 32:04.966
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

32:10.580 --> 32:12.887
Well, that won't do.

32:13.061 --> 32:15.063
- Will that do?
- No. Not at all.

32:16.891 --> 32:19.024
We are going to
throw you a wedding.

32:19.198 --> 32:21.156
A proper wedding.

32:21.330 --> 32:22.941
No. We decided
not to wait...

32:23.115 --> 32:24.551
Now. Here.

32:38.304 --> 32:39.348
[CHUCKLES]

32:42.525 --> 32:44.179
Surprise.

32:44.353 --> 32:45.964
[GASPS AND LAUGHS]

33:15.645 --> 33:16.690
You need a haircut.

33:16.864 --> 33:18.083
[CHUCKLES]

33:35.883 --> 33:37.406
I love you, son.

33:39.930 --> 33:41.584
[SPEAKING HEBREW]

33:44.500 --> 33:45.806
[VOICE BREAKING]
Goodbye, Dad.

33:48.417 --> 33:49.810
[PATS BACK]

34:27.935 --> 34:29.284
I got you something.

34:29.458 --> 34:30.764
I would assume so.

34:30.938 --> 34:32.373
You are invited
to a wedding.

34:32.547 --> 34:34.072
It would be rude
not to.

34:34.246 --> 34:35.203
Yes.

34:37.510 --> 34:42.167
These were passed down from
my great-great-grandparents.

34:42.341 --> 34:44.168
This was supposed to be
for Maddie.

34:52.393 --> 34:54.657
I'm glad you two will be
wearing them both.

35:00.968 --> 35:03.318
Was your father
a good father?

35:03.492 --> 35:06.365
He did his best.

35:06.539 --> 35:08.497
- Was he good?
- I don't know, Shaun.

35:08.671 --> 35:09.846
I... I loved him, I guess.

35:10.020 --> 35:11.892
Okay, but was he good?

35:12.066 --> 35:13.633
Shaun, I'm clearly trying
to avoid this question.

35:13.807 --> 35:15.591
My father's not around
to defend himself.

35:15.765 --> 35:17.419
- You know?
- I know.

35:17.593 --> 35:20.074
Can we go fishing again
sometime?

35:20.248 --> 35:21.684
I thought
you hated fishing.

35:28.126 --> 35:30.345
I'm cold.

35:30.519 --> 35:32.913
And wet.

35:33.087 --> 35:34.697
And very bored.

35:36.569 --> 35:38.223
It'll be a good memory.

35:49.582 --> 35:51.323
My father is
a very good father.

35:54.195 --> 35:55.327
Is?

35:58.852 --> 36:00.723
I love you,
Dr. Glassman.

36:06.599 --> 36:08.731
I love you, too,
Dr. Murphy.

36:16.652 --> 36:17.740
Maybe we should go with
the clip-on.

36:19.089 --> 36:20.700
Hmm.

36:20.874 --> 36:22.528
Oh.

36:25.531 --> 36:26.662
I've been lucky enough
to be given the training

36:26.836 --> 36:29.361
to save lives.

36:29.535 --> 36:32.668
But I don't think
I've ever felt
luckier than I do right now.

36:32.842 --> 36:34.540
Shaun Robert Murphy,

36:34.714 --> 36:36.019
do you take
Lea Abigail Dilallo...

36:36.194 --> 36:37.238
I do.

36:37.412 --> 36:40.023
[LAUGHTER]

36:40.198 --> 36:41.199
Oh.

36:41.373 --> 36:43.157
To have and to hold,

36:43.331 --> 36:45.464
to honor, to treasure,

36:45.638 --> 36:48.336
to be by her side
in sorrow and in joy,

36:48.510 --> 36:51.165
through good times
and the bad,

36:51.339 --> 36:53.428
and to love
and cherish her always?

36:53.602 --> 36:54.777
I do.

36:56.605 --> 36:59.217
Lea Abigail Dilallo,

